<div class="row">
  <section class="col col-720 col-space-l-top">
    <div class="inset">
      <p>Your initial teacher training (ITT) will take you on an incredible journey into the classroom.</p>
      <p>Exactly what you do during ITT will depend on the course you're on and the qualifications you're working towards. But all trainees get around 120 days of classroom experience, so you'll get to find out what life in the classroom is really like.</p>
      <p>You'll train to teach in at least 2 schools, usually for a minimum of 6 weeks each, so you'll have plenty of time to meet other teachers and become part of supportive school communities.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading--box-blue">Developing pupils</h2>
    <div class="inset">
      <p>During training, you'll get to find out what it takes to become the kind of teacher that pupils will remember years after leaving school.</p>
      <p>Your lessons will be unobserved and observed, giving you plenty of chances to see pupils experience 'aha' moments, when your teaching helps them learn something new.</p>
      <p>You'll be given the tools needed to inspire, motivate and challenge pupils. You'll learn how to adapt your teaching style to suit the strengths and needs of all pupils, and how to manage behaviour to create a positive learning environment.</p>
      <p>Ultimately, you'll get to see how your teaching can help pupils progress and get the outcomes you'll know they are capable of.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading--box-blue">Developing you</h2>
    <div class="inset">
      <p>You'll learn from teachers like you through taught sessions, seminars and workshops. You'll have the chance to get involved in academic or professional research so you can dig deeper into what makes you tick as a teacher.</p>
      <p>You'll be able to see how you're getting on by completing tasks and assignments, so you can track what you're learning as you teach. These will be a combination of less formal, ongoing assessments, and formal assessments that usually happen at the end of your course.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading--box-blue">Working with a mentor</h2>
    <div class="inset">
      <p>You won't be taking on this amazing challenge alone. You'll team up with a mentor to support you in your school placements. Your mentor will guide you through your training, sharing learning and career development opportunities with you.</p>
      <p>Your mentor will meet with you regularly to make sure your training is a positive experience.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
 </div>

